                                "text": "thanks for looking into this!\n\nhm, I don't recall why we (or probably I at that point) decided to go with rebase over merge, but it does have some advantages -- the most important one being: \"upstream is authoritative\".\nwhile resolving the git conflicts, we could always be sure that upstream is the source of truth and we should prefer that. keeping the git log linear with frequent (automated) updates from upstream mostly worked fine in the past years, except for a few edge cases -- and while I understand that this is super frustrating and I feel sorry for that, but it's not trivial for me to decide we should switch, so I recommend let's think about the consequences of switching from rebase to merge strategy, then well document this process and make the switch if that seems a brighter path "
                            },
