                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\none huge con against rebase is that we never actually push back to the upstream so we maintain a crazy divergent branch for a long time .. and yeah, when we need to babysit the rebase process, that actually goes through all the thousands of commits from weblate. switching to merge can mitigate some of that as the past doesn't need to be replayed, while git conflicts would still occur similarly, and the same problem could still hit us, so it's not a silver bullet."
